{"lemma":"زَفِرَةٍ","slug":"زَفِرَةٍ","root":"ز.ف.ر","root_slug":"ز-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ز-ف-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n17869","n17870"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B2%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to exhale","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to bray","tags":["intransitive"],"examples":[{"text":"زَفَرَ ٱلْحِمَارُ","english":"The donkey brayed."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/za.fa.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n17869","headword_ar":"زَفْرَةٌ","root":"zfr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A drawing-in of the breath to the utmost, by reason of distress:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a drawing-back of the breath vehemently, so that the ribs become swollen out:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1:)] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an emission of the breath after prolonging it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuforapN","text_ar":"زُفْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muzodafarN","text_ar":"مُزْدَفَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muzaf~arN","text_ar":"مُزَفَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muzofarN","text_ar":"مُزْفَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (as in a copy of the K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muzaf~arapN","text_ar":"مُزَفَّرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (CK, but omitted in the TA and in my MS. copy of the K:) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an emission of the breath with a prolonged sound;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sigh,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a long"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement sigh;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a groan:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an emission of the breath after filling the chest with it by reason of grief:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see, again, 1:)] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zafaraAtN","text_ar":"زَفَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because it is a subst., not an epithet; but sometimes, by poetic license,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaforaAtN","text_ar":"زَفْرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) El-Jaadee says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yarojiEo EalaY diq~apK walaAhaDami \n                      \n                     \n                        xiyTa EalaYzaforapK fatam~a walamo"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"As though he were sewed up after a drawing-in of the breath to the utmost, by reason of distress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"so that he seemed to be constantly so drawing in his breath, on account of the largeness of his belly, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and did not become restored to slenderness nor lankness of the belly."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S.) And another says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"fatasotariyHu Aln~afosu mino zaforaAtihaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And the soul finds rest from its drawing-in of the breath to the utmost, by reason of distress;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from its sighs, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b2-  Also, ↓ all the words above mentioned, [A man]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breathing"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the manner above described"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutanaf~isN","text_ar":"مُتَنَفِّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [unless this be a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutanaf~isN","text_ar":"مُتَنَفِّسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"breathing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as seems probable from the forms of more than one of these words, and from what follows, and also from an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muzodafarN","text_ar":"مُزْدَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] (K, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaforapN","text_ar":"زَفْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zuforapN","text_ar":"زُفْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, * TA [but not the other words mentioned above, as is implied in the CK,]) The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"middle"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) of a thing, (K,) or of a horse: (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zafaraAtN","text_ar":"زَفَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) One says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laEaZiymu Alz~uforapi","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَعَظِيمُ الزُّفْرَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is great in the middle:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the chest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"belly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  One says also, of a camel, or other beast,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^a$ad~a zaforatahu","text_ar":"مَا اَشَدَّ زَفْرَتَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How strong is the knitting together of his joints!"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n17870","headword_ar":"زُفْرَةٌ","root":"zfr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zaforapN","text_ar":"زَفْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}